      "type": "dashboard_panel",
      "prompt": {
        "positive": "A visual timeline showing the progress of a software build through its key phases: discovery, design, architecture, frontend, backend, integration, testing, and deployment. Each phase should have a status indicator (pending, active, completed, failed) along with a brief explanation of what that phase entails. The panel should use a dark color scheme with clear, readable typography.",
        "negative": "Avoid overly complex or flashy visualizations. Do not include any placeholder text or images - the panel should display real build data."
